txt.en: Orcs of the White Hand press their invasion of Wildermore by utilizing an icy roadway through the Balewood.\n\nThe Orcs must be slain if any peace is to return to the Balewood.
You have slain a significant number of Orcs along the path. Their numbers will recover in time, but you have dealt them a harsh blow and slowed their assaults into the High Knolls and Whitshaws.
Orcs of Isengard attempt to transport lumber from the Balewood to Orthanc, but are hindered by Wood-trolls and the unnatural snow and cold.
You have defeated many Orcs in the Balewood.
The Orcs of the Balewood are a mighty force and their numbers must be thinned if the Rohirrim of Wildermore are to seize the advantage.
Orcs of the White Hand press their invasion of Wildermore by utilising an icy roadway through Balewood. The Orcs must be slain if any peace is to return to Balewood.
